The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, July 05, 2004 				 MTNL-BSNL merger option to be explored
																								New Delhi, July 4 (PTI): The plan for a possible merger of MTNL and BSNL is likely to be discussed at a meeting called by the department of telecom on July 7.																								According to sources, the meeting will discuss the possibility of merger of the two public-sector companies as well as the viability of various options proposed. 																								A senior official of the department was told to prepare a note in this regard.																								Union IT and communications minister Dayanidhi Maran is scheduled to be present along with other senior officials. Sources added the meeting could be just another exploratory one for looking at the merger in view of the gigantic tasks and hurdles involved with it. Earlier, such a meeting was held in May.																								On July 6 and 7, the department is also holding interviews for the selection of a chairman for BSNL. 
